		<div class="comment-body"><p>You mean saute isn&#8217;t a generic term for cooking on a stovetop in a saute pan/skillet in a small amount of oil over medium to high heat?  I do this all the time, so I use saute frequently.  Is there a different word/short phrase that means the same thing?</p>
<p>If I&#8217;d gone through and followed these rules from the start, it would probably be much easier to convert to the google recipe format, too.</p>
<p>Were I to ever want to go the cookbook route, I&#8217;d definitely need to recruit someone to stand over my shoulder and time things.  I can remember all of the ingredients and the process, but I have no sense at all of how long things have taken.</p>
