		<div class="comment-body"><p>And I thought I was doing just fine, compared to my grandmother&#8217;s recipes: &#8220;Make the batter thicker than for pancakes, but denser than for bread.&#8221; Or, &#8220;Add as much flour as necessary.&#8221;<br />
I understand that we now write for strangers, and not for a handful of our equally skilled neighbors who need reminders, more than exact directions.<br />
Thanks for the &#8220;cheat sheet&#8221;. It makes it much less confusing and mysterious. I always appreciate such handy tools, even though I am enamored with the word &#8220;saute&#8221;:)</p>
</div>

