			<img alt='' src='http://2.gravatar.com/avatar/2aa409c65291016c7faf843521d066aa?s=40&amp;d=identicon&amp;r=PG' class='avatar avatar-40' height='40' width='40' />			<cite class="fn"><a href='http://diet' rel='external nofollow' class='url'>Ricki</a></cite> <span class="says">says:</span>		</div><!-- .comment-author .vcard -->
		
		<div class="comment-meta commentmetadata"><a href="http://justcooknyc.com/2011/04/14/recipe-writing-cheat-sheet/#comment-6443">
			April 14, 2011 at 1:38 pm</a>		</div><!-- .comment-meta .commentmetadata -->

		<div class="comment-body"><p>Great tips&#8211;thanks.  Re: numbers 8 and 9, this is where paying attention in those high school English classes would have come in handy.  Anyone who knows their grammar would never make a mistake with that one (adjective before noun describes that noun&#8211;so &#8220;CHOPPED mushrooms&#8221; means the mushrooms must already be chopped for this word order).  <img src='http://s1.wp.com/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_wink.gif?m=1129645325g' alt=';)' class='wp-smiley' /> </p>
</div>

